- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper introduces a new decomposition technique for graphs on surfaces, which is a topic closely related to computational geometry.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithm.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the subgraph isomorphism problem has applications in game theory and social network analysis.
